Description: Provides an R interface to the Python package 'u-stats' for
    efficient computation of higher-order U-statistics using Einstein
    summation notation. The package automatically converts R objects to
    NumPy or PyTorch tensors via 'reticulate' and supports GPU acceleration
    when PyTorch with CUDA is available. Designed for large-scale statistical
    estimation where numerical stability and performance are critical.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    reticulate
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.11)
Config/reticulate:
    packages:
        - u-stats
        - numpy
        - torch
